  "response": "There is no verified evidence that Saddam Hussein and Osama bin Laden collaborated in the 9/11 attacks. This conclusion has been supported by multiple investigations conducted by U.S. intelligence agencies and the 9/11 Commission. The 9/11 Commission Report, released in 2004, specifically stated that there was no credible evidence of a collaborative relationship between Iraq and al-Qaeda with regard to the attacks. Osama bin Laden led al-Qaeda, the terrorist group responsible for the 9/11 attacks, and they operated independently from the Iraqi government led by Saddam Hussein.",
